Note:
STREAM - Lazy Sequence Tier 0 Primitive

This file implements a pull-based lazy sequence. Since the bootstrap
stage1 does not yet expose first-class function values, we use a
discriminated-union representation: each Stream carries an integer
"kind" tag and a small set of integer parameters that fully define
its behavior.

Kinds:
  1 = RANGE_INC      [start, end, step]   yields start, start+step, ... while value < end
  2 = REPEAT_VAL     [value]              yields value forever
  3 = ITERATE_ARITH  [seed, increment]    yields seed, seed+inc, seed+2*inc, ... (infinite)
  4 = FROM_LIST      [list_ptr, index]    yields list elements starting at index
  5 = TAKE           [src_stream, n_left]
  6 = DROP           [src_stream, n_left]
  7 = MAP_ADD        [src_stream, delta]  applies (x + delta)
  8 = MAP_MUL        [src_stream, factor] applies (x * factor)
  9 = FILTER_EQ      [src_stream, target] yields only elements equal to target
 10 = FILTER_GT      [src_stream, threshold]
 11 = FILTER_LT      [src_stream, threshold]
 12 = CONCAT         [src_a, src_b, phase] phase 0 = consuming a, 1 = consuming b
 13 = ZIP_ADD        [src_a, src_b]       yields a+b until either ends

Stream record (48 bytes):
  offset 0:  kind
  offset 8:  param0
  offset 16: param1
  offset 24: param2
  offset 32: refcount
  offset 40: terminated flag (1 if stream has produced its last value)

The integer-coded transforms cover the common Stream API surface
(map/filter/take/drop/zip/concat) without requiring first-class
closures.
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List

Let STREAM_SIZE be 48
Let STREAM_KIND_RANGE be 1
Let STREAM_KIND_REPEAT be 2
Let STREAM_KIND_ITERATE be 3
Let STREAM_KIND_FROM_LIST be 4
Let STREAM_KIND_TAKE be 5
Let STREAM_KIND_DROP be 6
Let STREAM_KIND_MAP_ADD be 7
Let STREAM_KIND_MAP_MUL be 8
Let STREAM_KIND_FILTER_EQ be 9
Let STREAM_KIND_FILTER_GT be 10
Let STREAM_KIND_FILTER_LT be 11
Let STREAM_KIND_CONCAT be 12
Let STREAM_KIND_ZIP_ADD be 13
Let STREAM_END_SENTINEL be -99999999999

@Reasoning
Allocate a fresh stream node.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
48-byte alloc; set kind/param0/param1/param2; refcount = 1, terminated
= 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: 48 bytes.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "stream_alloc" takes kind as Integer, p0 as Integer, p1 as Integer, p2 as Integer returns Integer:
    Let s be proc allocate from Layout with STREAM_SIZE
    If s is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 0, kind
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 8, p0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 16, p1
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 24, p2
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 32, 1
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 40, 0
    Return s
End Process

@Reasoning
Construct a half-open range stream [start, end) with step.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
RANGE_INC kind with params (start, end, step).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: 48 bytes.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "stream_range" takes start as Integer, end as Integer, step as Integer returns Integer:
    If step is equal to 0:
        Set step to 1
    End If
    Return proc stream_alloc with STREAM_KIND_RANGE, start, end, step
End Process

@Reasoning
Infinite stream that repeats one value.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
REPEAT_VAL kind with params (value, 0, 0).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "stream_repeat" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc stream_alloc with STREAM_KIND_REPEAT, value, 0, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Infinite arithmetic sequence: seed, seed+inc, seed+2*inc, ...
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
ITERATE_ARITH kind with params (seed, inc, 0).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "stream_iterate" takes seed as Integer, inc as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc stream_alloc with STREAM_KIND_ITERATE, seed, inc, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Stream from a list, in order.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
FROM_LIST kind with params (list_ptr, index = 0, 0).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "stream_from_list" takes list_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc stream_alloc with STREAM_KIND_FROM_LIST, list_ptr, 0, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Take at most n elements from source stream.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
TAKE wrapper around src with countdown.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) per construction.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "stream_take" takes src as Integer, n as Integer returns Integer:
    If src is not equal to 0:
        Let rc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with src, 32
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with src, 32, rc plus 1
    End If
    Return proc stream_alloc with STREAM_KIND_TAKE, src, n, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Drop the first n elements of source then continue.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
DROP wrapper; n is decremented on each consumption from source.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) per construction; O(n) per first pull.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "stream_drop" takes src as Integer, n as Integer returns Integer:
    If src is not equal to 0:
        Let rc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with src, 32
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with src, 32, rc plus 1
    End If
    Return proc stream_alloc with STREAM_KIND_DROP, src, n, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Map each value to (value + delta).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
MAP_ADD wrapper.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) per element when consumed.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "stream_map_add" takes src as Integer, delta as Integer returns Integer:
    If src is not equal to 0:
        Let rc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with src, 32
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with src, 32, rc plus 1
    End If
    Return proc stream_alloc with STREAM_KIND_MAP_ADD, src, delta, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Map each value to (value * factor).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
MAP_MUL wrapper.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) per element.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "stream_map_mul" takes src as Integer, factor as Integer returns Integer:
    If src is not equal to 0:
        Let rc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with src, 32
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with src, 32, rc plus 1
    End If
    Return proc stream_alloc with STREAM_KIND_MAP_MUL, src, factor, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Filter to elements equal to target.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
FILTER_EQ wrapper.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: amortized O(1) per yielded element, with skip-loop for filtering.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "stream_filter_eq" takes src as Integer, target as Integer returns Integer:
    If src is not equal to 0:
        Let rc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with src, 32
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with src, 32, rc plus 1
    End If
    Return proc stream_alloc with STREAM_KIND_FILTER_EQ, src, target, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Filter to elements greater than threshold.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
FILTER_GT wrapper.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: amortized O(1) per yielded element.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "stream_filter_gt" takes src as Integer, threshold as Integer returns Integer:
    If src is not equal to 0:
        Let rc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with src, 32
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with src, 32, rc plus 1
    End If
    Return proc stream_alloc with STREAM_KIND_FILTER_GT, src, threshold, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Filter to elements less than threshold.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
FILTER_LT wrapper.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: amortized O(1) per yielded element.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "stream_filter_lt" takes src as Integer, threshold as Integer returns Integer:
    If src is not equal to 0:
        Let rc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with src, 32
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with src, 32, rc plus 1
    End If
    Return proc stream_alloc with STREAM_KIND_FILTER_LT, src, threshold, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Concatenate two streams: yield a's values, then b's.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
CONCAT wrapper with phase = 0 (consuming a).
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) per element.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "stream_concat" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is not equal to 0:
        Let rc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with a, 32
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with a, 32, rc plus 1
    End If
    If b is not equal to 0:
        Let rc2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with b, 32
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with b, 32, rc2 plus 1
    End If
    Return proc stream_alloc with STREAM_KIND_CONCAT, a, b, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Zip two streams by adding their elements pairwise.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
ZIP_ADD wrapper.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) per element.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "stream_zip_add" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is not equal to 0:
        Let rc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with a, 32
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with a, 32, rc plus 1
    End If
    If b is not equal to 0:
        Let rc2 be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with b, 32
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with b, 32, rc2 plus 1
    End If
    Return proc stream_alloc with STREAM_KIND_ZIP_ADD, a, b, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Pull the next element from the stream. Returns STREAM_END_SENTINEL
when the stream is exhausted. The sentinel is INT64_MIN+1 so it
cannot be a legitimate yielded value for any practical purpose.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Dispatch on kind:
- RANGE_INC: check current vs end; advance start; produce.
- REPEAT_VAL: always yield param0.
- ITERATE_ARITH: yield param0, then advance by param1.
- FROM_LIST: read list[index], advance index; terminate at length.
- TAKE: if n_left == 0, end; else pull from src, decrement n.
- DROP: if n_left > 0, pull-and-discard n times then pull and yield.
- MAP_ADD / MAP_MUL: pull from src, transform, yield.
- FILTER_EQ / FILTER_GT / FILTER_LT: pull-skip-loop until predicate
  satisfied or src ends.
- CONCAT: pull from a until end, then b.
- ZIP_ADD: pull one from each; end if either ends.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1) amortized for most kinds; O(filter-skip-distance) for
filters.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller must hold a reference to the stream.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "stream_next" takes s as Integer returns Integer:
    If s is equal to 0:
        Return STREAM_END_SENTINEL
    End If
    Let terminated be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 40
    If terminated is equal to 1:
        Return STREAM_END_SENTINEL
    End If
    Let kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 0
    If kind is equal to STREAM_KIND_RANGE:
        Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 8
        Let end be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 16
        Let step be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 24
        If cur is greater than or equal to end:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 40, 1
            Return STREAM_END_SENTINEL
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 8, cur plus step
        Return cur
    End If
    If kind is equal to STREAM_KIND_REPEAT:
        Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 8
    End If
    If kind is equal to STREAM_KIND_ITERATE:
        Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 8
        Let inc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 16
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 8, cur plus inc
        Return cur
    End If
    If kind is equal to STREAM_KIND_FROM_LIST:
        Let list_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 8
        Let idx be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 16
        Let len be proc list_length from List with list_ptr
        If idx is greater than or equal to len:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 40, 1
            Return STREAM_END_SENTINEL
        End If
        Let v be proc list_get from List with list_ptr, idx
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 16, idx plus 1
        Return v
    End If
    If kind is equal to STREAM_KIND_TAKE:
        Let src be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 8
        Let n_left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 16
        If n_left is less than or equal to 0:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 40, 1
            Return STREAM_END_SENTINEL
        End If
        Let v be proc stream_next with src
        If v is equal to STREAM_END_SENTINEL:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 40, 1
            Return STREAM_END_SENTINEL
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 16, n_left minus 1
        Return v
    End If
    If kind is equal to STREAM_KIND_DROP:
        Let src be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 8
        Let n_left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 16
        While n_left is greater than 0:
            Let drop_v be proc stream_next with src
            If drop_v is equal to STREAM_END_SENTINEL:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 16, 0
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 40, 1
                Return STREAM_END_SENTINEL
            End If
            Set n_left to n_left minus 1
        End While
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 16, 0
        Let v be proc stream_next with src
        If v is equal to STREAM_END_SENTINEL:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 40, 1
        End If
        Return v
    End If
    If kind is equal to STREAM_KIND_MAP_ADD:
        Let src be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 8
        Let delta be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 16
        Let v be proc stream_next with src
        If v is equal to STREAM_END_SENTINEL:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 40, 1
            Return STREAM_END_SENTINEL
        End If
        Return v plus delta
    End If
    If kind is equal to STREAM_KIND_MAP_MUL:
        Let src be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 8
        Let factor be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 16
        Let v be proc stream_next with src
        If v is equal to STREAM_END_SENTINEL:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 40, 1
            Return STREAM_END_SENTINEL
        End If
        Return v multiplied by factor
    End If
    If kind is equal to STREAM_KIND_FILTER_EQ:
        Let src be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 8
        Let target be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 16
        While 1 is equal to 1:
            Let v be proc stream_next with src
            If v is equal to STREAM_END_SENTINEL:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 40, 1
                Return STREAM_END_SENTINEL
            End If
            If v is equal to target:
                Return v
            End If
        End While
    End If
    If kind is equal to STREAM_KIND_FILTER_GT:
        Let src be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 8
        Let threshold be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 16
        While 1 is equal to 1:
            Let v be proc stream_next with src
            If v is equal to STREAM_END_SENTINEL:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 40, 1
                Return STREAM_END_SENTINEL
            End If
            If v is greater than threshold:
                Return v
            End If
        End While
    End If
    If kind is equal to STREAM_KIND_FILTER_LT:
        Let src be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 8
        Let threshold be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 16
        While 1 is equal to 1:
            Let v be proc stream_next with src
            If v is equal to STREAM_END_SENTINEL:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 40, 1
                Return STREAM_END_SENTINEL
            End If
            If v is less than threshold:
                Return v
            End If
        End While
    End If
    If kind is equal to STREAM_KIND_CONCAT:
        Let phase be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 24
        If phase is equal to 0:
            Let a be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 8
            Let v be proc stream_next with a
            If v is not equal to STREAM_END_SENTINEL:
                Return v
            End If
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 24, 1
            Let b be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 16
            Let v2 be proc stream_next with b
            If v2 is equal to STREAM_END_SENTINEL:
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 40, 1
            End If
            Return v2
        End If
        Let b be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 16
        Let v be proc stream_next with b
        If v is equal to STREAM_END_SENTINEL:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 40, 1
        End If
        Return v
    End If
    If kind is equal to STREAM_KIND_ZIP_ADD:
        Let a be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 8
        Let b be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with s, 16
        Let va be proc stream_next with a
        If va is equal to STREAM_END_SENTINEL:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 40, 1
            Return STREAM_END_SENTINEL
        End If
        Let vb be proc stream_next with b
        If vb is equal to STREAM_END_SENTINEL:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 40, 1
            Return STREAM_END_SENTINEL
        End If
        Return va plus vb
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with s, 40, 1
    Return STREAM_END_SENTINEL
End Process

@Reasoning
Collect all elements of stream into the supplied list. Care must be
taken: an infinite stream will run forever; callers should chain
with stream_take first.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Pull elements via stream_next until END_SENTINEL, appending each to
out_list.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller must ensure the stream is finite.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "stream_collect_to_list" takes s as Integer, out_list as Integer returns Integer:
    If s is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If out_list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let v be proc stream_next with s
        If v is equal to STREAM_END_SENTINEL:
            Return 1
        End If
        proc list_append from List with out_list, v
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Release the stream and any child streams it holds.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Iterative recursive release: decrement refcount; if zero, recurse
into the stream's child references (param0 and param1 are pointers
for combinators) by appending them to a work stack.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(chain depth).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller-owned.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "stream_destroy" takes s as Integer returns Integer:
    If s is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cap be 32
    Let buf_bytes be cap multiplied by 8
    Let buf be proc allocate from Layout with buf_bytes
    If buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let sp be 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with buf, 0, s
    Set sp to 1
    While sp is greater than 0:
        Set sp to sp minus 1
        Let off be sp multiplied by 8
        Let node be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with buf, off
        Let rc be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, 32
        Let new_rc be rc minus 1
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, 32, new_rc
        If new_rc is equal to 0:
            Let kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, 0
            Let has_p0 be 0
            Let has_p1 be 0
            If kind is greater than or equal to STREAM_KIND_TAKE:
                Set has_p0 to 1
            End If
            If kind is equal to STREAM_KIND_CONCAT:
                Set has_p1 to 1
            End If
            If kind is equal to STREAM_KIND_ZIP_ADD:
                Set has_p1 to 1
            End If
            If has_p0 is equal to 1:
                Let p0 be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, 8
                If p0 is not equal to 0:
                    Let need be sp plus 1
                    If need is greater than cap:
                        Let new_cap be cap multiplied by 2
                        Let new_bytes be new_cap multiplied by 8
                        Let new_buf be proc allocate from Layout with new_bytes
                        If new_buf is equal to 0:
                            proc deallocate from Layout with buf
                            Return 0
                        End If
                        Let copy_bytes be cap multiplied by 8
                        proc memory_copy from Memory with new_buf, buf, copy_bytes
                        proc deallocate from Layout with buf
                        Set buf to new_buf
                        Set cap to new_cap
                    End If
                    Let s_off be sp multiplied by 8
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with buf, s_off, p0
                    Set sp to sp plus 1
                End If
            End If
            If has_p1 is equal to 1:
                Let p1 be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, 16
                If p1 is not equal to 0:
                    Let need be sp plus 1
                    If need is greater than cap:
                        Let new_cap be cap multiplied by 2
                        Let new_bytes be new_cap multiplied by 8
                        Let new_buf be proc allocate from Layout with new_bytes
                        If new_buf is equal to 0:
                            proc deallocate from Layout with buf
                            Return 0
                        End If
                        Let copy_bytes be cap multiplied by 8
                        proc memory_copy from Memory with new_buf, buf, copy_bytes
                        proc deallocate from Layout with buf
                        Set buf to new_buf
                        Set cap to new_cap
                    End If
                    Let s_off be sp multiplied by 8
                    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with buf, s_off, p1
                    Set sp to sp plus 1
                End If
            End If
            proc deallocate from Layout with node
        End If
    End While
    proc deallocate from Layout with buf
    Return 1
End Process
